    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-21T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-21T11:45:00-05:00" n="351"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810. 79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./337:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-21T11:00:00-05:45"
                            >March 21, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Pan American Airways and All American Cables revised contracts passed by
                    Congress and signed by President yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
